New Records: Alex Sarr has the second-most blocks of any teenager for the first eight games to start his career, with only Karl-Anthony Towns having more.
Key Match Events: Kyshawn George made four 3-pointers in the second quarter en route to a 15-point performance on an efficient 5 of 9 from the field.
Alex Sarr recorded two blocks and a steal, continuing to be a defensive presence.
Post-Match Reflections: Wizards coach Brian Keefe praised Kyshawn George for playing within himself and making shots.
Keefe also commented on Alex Sarr's growth and learning, highlighting his defensive contributions and the need for team support.
